ow to develop a professional style, get started on a piece of writing, create a first draft, and edit it into a strong final product. She then offers practical advice on more than a dozen forms of writing, from emails and slide decks to proposals and cover letters. Along the way, Coven provides a wealth of concrete examples and simple templates that make the concepts easy to understand and apply.Based on Coven’s popular writing classes and workshops at Princeton University as well as her decades of experience in the public and private sectors, Writing on the Job addresses the real challenges professionals face in today’s digital age, and shares essential practices that can improve the performance of any organization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBusiness communication. 0aBusiness report writing. 0aBusiness writing. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Style Manuals.2bisacsh  aBusiness model.  aCareer.  aClassroom.  aColumbia Business School.  aCommunication.  aCoven.  aDecision-making.  aInvestor.  aJournal of Applied Corporate Finance.  aLearning.  aNewspaper.  aNonprofit organization.  aPerformance appraisal.  aPrivate sector.  aPublic sector.  aPublishing.  aSkill.  aWealth.  aWorkplace.  aWriter.  aWriting.  aYear.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022 Englishz978311099370708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022z9783110993684oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107497310 cprintz978069122995940uh